<title>Adiós a los cuadrados</title>

<statement>
  <p>[@@@@@@@@@]</p>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ol>
      <li>44 square units. Sample response: <m>7 \times 5 = 35, 3 \times 3 = 9, 35 + 9 = 44</m></li>
      <li>32 square units. Sample response: I broke it into a smaller <m>4 \times 2</m> rectangle at the bottom and a bigger <m>3 \times 8</m> rectangle at the top and added <m>8 + 24</m>. I counted the spaces between the tick marks like on a number line to find the side lengths.</li>
    </ol>
  </solution>


